openpa
------------------------------------------
The goal of this project is to provide an open source, highly-portable library
that provides atomic primitives (and related constructs) for high performance,
concurrent software. This project is a collaboration between the Mathematics
and Computer Science (MCS) division at Argonne National Laboratory (ANL) and
the HDF Group. The code was originally derived from work on the MPICH2
project.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.4-1
  cygwin-devel-2.0.4-1
  libopa-devel-1.0.4-1bl1
  libopa1-1.0.4-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://trac.mpich.org/projects/openpa/

Canonical download:
  http://trac.mpich.org/projects/openpa/raw-attachment/wiki/Downloads/openpa-1.0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack openpa-1.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./openpa-1.0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/openpa-1.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/openpa-1.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopa1-1.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopa-devel-1.0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

